          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the first step before roof repair or replacement in Ball Ground?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Start with an inspection-first roof assessment. Inspector Roofing documents visible roof conditions before recommending repair, replacement, storm documentation, financing resources, commercial roofing, or insurance-related next steps."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does Inspector Roofing help with insurance documentation in Ball Ground?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Inspector Roofing helps organize insurance-ready roof documentation, photos, measurements when appropriate, storm indicators, repairability information, and claim-context details. The company does not act as a public adjuster, interpret policy coverage, negotiate claims, or guarantee claim approval."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can Inspector Roofing repair roofs in Ball Ground?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Repair needs may include leaks, missing shingles, flashing, pipe boots, lifted shingles, wind-related concerns, storm-related repairs, and emergency protection."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do you replace residential roofs in Ball Ground?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Inspector Roofing helps homeowners plan roof replacement with shingle selection, code-to-spec scope review, ventilation, accessories, cleanup, property protection, financing resources, and documentation."
          }
        },
        {
